Salé — The first instance criminal chamber for terrorism affairs at the annexe of Salé's appeal court handed on Thursday verdicts ranging from to 2 to 10 years in prison with no remission to 11 suspects sued in separate terrorism-related cases. The court sentenced a suspect to 10 years in jail for participating in an association to prepare and perpetrate terror acts, incitement to commit acts constituting terror acts, apology of terrorist acts and non-denunciation of terrorist acts. In another case involving three people, the court gave sentences ranging between 5 and 8 years and sentenced three suspects to three years in prison. The court also sentenced four other defendants to two years imprisonment.